The paper deals with the problem of recovering Gaussian vectors from modulo wrapped measurements, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a low-complexity iterative decoding algorithm, which involves optimization and statistical inference, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions quantization and analog-to-digital conversion, which are topics in multimedia and networking, respectively, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible sub-categories as well.
